    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black. This example features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, utilizing individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to produce a linear power band peaking at an 8,000 RPM redline. The powertrain is mated to a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-variable differential lock for precise torque vectoring. This vehicle has undergone rigorous preventative maintenance, including a reinforced rear subframe, rod bearing replacement with ARP hardware, and a comprehensive VANOS overhaul. The chassis remains taut with factory-spec bushings and dampers, ensuring the telepathic handling characteristics this platform is known for. The paint depth is consistent across all panels, and the interior Nappa leather remains supple with no bolster wear, reflecting its collector-quality status.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
